{
  "title": "Deploying Cron-Driven Tasks Using FastAPI with Python 3.12+",
  "summary": "This guide explains how to create and schedule cron-like jobs for recurring tasks within a FastAPI application using the `aiohttp_cron` package in Python 3.12+.",

  "key_points": [
    "Install the required packages: FastAPI, Uvicorn, and aiohttp_cron",
    "Create a new FastAPI application",
    "Define an asynchronous function for the recurring task",
    "Set up cron-like scheduling using `aiohttp_cron`",
    "Start the application with Uvicorn and register the scheduled task",
    "Monitor and manage the scheduled tasks"
  ],

  "code_examples": [
    {
      "language": "python",
      "code": "```\n\n# Install required packages:\n\npiпип install fastapi uvicorn aiohttp-cron\n\nimport asyncio\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, BackgroundTasks\nfrom aiohttp_cron import CronManager\n\napp = FastAPI()\nmanager = CronManager()\n\n# Define an asynchronous function for the recurring task\nasynchronous def scheduled_task():\n    # Your recurring task code here\n\n@app.on_event('startup')\ndef startup():\n    # Register the scheduled task with aiohttp_cron\n    background_tasks = BackgroundTasks(app)\n    manager.cron_jobs().add(name='scheduled_task', task=scheduled_task, time='*/5 * * * *', UTC=True)\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    uvicorn.run(app, host='0.0.0.0', port=8000, log_level='info')\n```"
    }
  ],

  "version_notes": [
    "This tutorial is tailored for Python 3.12+ and uses FastAPI v0.70.0 and aiohttp_cron v22.1.0."
  ],

  "caveats": [
    "Ensure your system has the necessary packages installed.",
    "Adjust the time format in the `time` argument of `cron_jobs().add()` according to the cron syntax.",
    "Monitor and manage your scheduled tasks as needed."
  ]
